<refentry id="fn_soap_current_url">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>soap_current_url</refentrytitle>
    <refmiscinfo>soap</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>soap_current_url</refname>
    <refpurpose>Returns URL used to access particular HTTP resource.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <funcsynopsis id="fsyn_soap_current_url">
      <funcprototype id="fproto_soap_current_url">
        <funcdef>varchar <function>soap_current_url</function></funcdef>
	<paramdef/>
      </funcprototype>
    </funcsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1 id="desc_soap_current_url"><title>Description</title>
      <para>
	  This function is used to get in VSP/VSPX context the 
	  URL used to access current resource (page). It check whether
	  'Host' header field is specified, if not will return as a  
	  host information the IP address resolved via connected socket 
	  information.
  </para>
</refsect1>
  <refsect1 id="ret_soap_current_url"><title>Return Types</title>
      <para>The return type of <function>soap_current_url()</function> is an string 
	  containing the URL of the HTTP request. 
      </para>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>



